✅ Do’s
Think before posting—ensure your content is respectful and appropriate.
Use privacy settings to control who can see your posts and personal information.
Verify information before sharing to avoid spreading fake news.
Maintain a professional digital image, especially on platforms like LinkedIn.
Be respectful in comments and messages—practice good online etiquette.
❌ Don’ts
Don’t share personal or sensitive information (address, phone number, bank details).
Don’t engage in cyberbullying, trolling, or online arguments.
Don’t post content that could harm your reputation or future career.
Don’t click on suspicious links or download unknown attachments.
Don’t overshare your location or daily routine publicly.
